interpretations of restrictions involving foreign national
HB214 INTRODUCED
85 campaign activities pursuant to 52 U.S.C. § 30121 where the
86 provisions are comparable to avoid federal and state
87 regulatory confusion and to minimize administrative burdens.
88 Other terms not specifically defined by the Alabama Fair
89 Campaign Practices Act, such as "independent expenditure,"
90 should likewise be construed.
91 (c) For purposes of this section, the following terms
92 have the following meanings:
93 (1) DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY. Acting either alone or
94 jointly with, through, or on behalf of any other noncandidate
95 election committee, political party, political action
96 committee, or principal campaign committee, organization,
97 person, or other entity.
98 (2) FOREIGN NATIONAL. a. Includes any of the following:
99 1. An individual who is not a citizen or lawful
100 permanent resident of the United States.
101 2. A government or subdivision of a foreign country or
102 municipality thereof.
103 3. A foreign political party.
104 4. Any entity, such as a partnership, association,
105 corporation, organization, or other combination of persons,
106 that is organized under the laws of, or has its principal
107 place of business in, a foreign country.
108 5. Any U.S. entity, such as a partnership, association,
109 corporation, or organization, which is wholly or majority
110 owned by any foreign national, unless: (i) any contribution or
111 expenditure the entity makes derives entirely from funds
112 generated by the entity's U.S. operations; and (ii) all
Page 4

generated by the entity's U.S. operations; and (ii) all
