113 decisions concerning the contributions or expenditures are
114 made by individuals who are U.S. citizens or permanent
115 residents, except decisions setting overall budget amounts.
116 b. The definition of "foreign national" should be
117 construed in pari materia with 52 U.S.C. § 30121 and the
118 regulations, interpretations, and guidance issued by the
119 Federal Election Commission pursuant to that law.
120 (3) NONCANDIDATE ELECTION. A question or proposition to
121 be placed before the voter in a state or local election, other
122 than the nomination or election of a candidate for public
123 office, such as a constitutional amendment or referendum."
124 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
125 1, 2026.
